## Key Findings (Task #850)
- 2 CD subtypes (n=16 vs n=34) are molecularly, not clinically, defined. No significant Montreal/CRP/HBI/age associations (all p>0.3).
- CMTF loadings dominated by canonical CD dysbiosis taxa: F. prausnitzii, Bacteroides spp, E. coli, R. torques, Subdoligranulum, E. rectale, R. intestinalis.
- 10 species differentially abundant between subtypes (p<0.05): B. salyersiae, Peptostreptococcaceae, P. johnsonii, P. xylaniphila, B. pseudocatenulatum, C. hathewayi, C. bolteae, R. hominis, R. bromii.
- CRITICAL: Only 592/81,867 metabolites annotated (0.7%). Tryptophan-NAD and BCAA axes score 0.0 — cannot assess.
- Bifidobacterium-TCDCA axis: subtype 0 = 1.03, subtype 1 = 1.19 (species markers only). B. pseudocatenulatum differential + taurine degradation enrichment in subtype 0 = suggestive evidence.
- No pathway FDR<0.1 (414 pathways, n=50). Nominally: L-glutamate degradation, L-ascorbate biosynthesis, taurine degradation enriched in subtype 0.
- Subtype 1 has dense species-metabolite network (23,610 edges); subtype 0 sparse (5 edges, low power).
- Pipeline bug: scipy.stats.kruskal fails with constant values in crohns_subtype_characterization.py clinical_associations(). Worked around by calling pieces manually.

## Technical Notes
- API auth: use X-API-Key header with key from .env. HMP2 data alignment: use 2-omic (species+metabolomics) not 3-omic.
- Load with diagnosis_filter=["CD","nonIBD"], align, then filter to CD-only post-alignment.
- Pathway sample IDs have _P_pathabundance_cpm suffix — must strip before alignment.
- Metabolite annotations available in data/hmp2/HMP2_metabolomics_w_metadata.biom.gz (JSON biom with rows[].metadata.Metabolite).
- Results: output/crohns/microbiome-metabolome-subtyping/biological_validation_results.json + per-subtype CSVs.

